1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper focuses on studying information-theoretic limits for SWIPT systems, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers a three-node system and analyzes the performance of the system under different constraints, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless information and power transfer, which is a topic related to networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the efficiency of wireless power transfer, which is a topic related to multimedia systems. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses Hermite polynomial bases to prove the optimality of the capacity-achieving input distribution, which falls under the scope of computational engineering.
